## What This Codebase Is

A design operating system for musical instrument manufacturing.
Stack: Vue 3 + TypeScript + FastAPI + SQLAlchemy + Pinia.
Every feature orbits a single object: InstrumentProjectData (services/api/app/schemas/instrument_project.py).

## The Four Layers — Never Violate These

Layer 0 — Project Graph (schemas/instrument_project.py)
  The single source of design truth. Stored in Project.data JSONB.
  API: GET/PUT /api/projects/{id}/design-state

Layer 1 — Engines (instrument_geometry/, materials/, analyzer/, acoustic_engine/)
  Pure computation. No UI. No Pinia. No database calls. No Vue imports.
  Tested in isolation. Accepts inputs, returns outputs.

Layer 2 — Workspaces (instrument-workspace/, design-intake/, manufacturing/)
  Where builders spend time. Reads project state, supports local editing,
  commits explicitly via PUT /api/projects/{id}/design-state.
  NEVER auto-saves derived values.

Layer 3 — Utilities (design-utilities/)
  Stateless calculators. Standalone mode + project context mode.
  NEVER auto-writes to project state.

## The Golden Rule

No feature bypasses the Instrument Project Graph.
Every feature: reads from project state → derives computed values → suggests
advisory recommendations → commits explicit user-confirmed writes.

## Hard Boundaries — Never Cross These

FORBIDDEN in analyzer/:
  from app.cam.*
  from app.rmos.*
  from tap_tone_pi.*   # contract only via viewer_pack_v1

FORBIDDEN in engines (Layer 1):
  Any Vue import
  Any Pinia import
  Any direct database call
  Any router import

FORBIDDEN in any workspace:
  Math/calculation logic (belongs in Layer 1 engine)
  Direct species/material data (fetch from /api/system/materials/tonewoods)
  Auto-saving derived values (user must confirm all writes)

